         <fn id="d22e218a1310">
            <label>6</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d22e225" publication-type="other">
Tim Congdon, in his evidence to the Treasury and Civil Service Committee of the House of Commons,
reprinted as Lombard Street Research Occasional Paper no. 1, July 1989, cites the relatively rapid growth
rate of housing finance in the UK as compared with Germany as causing problems for ERM membership,
but he attributes the growth differential largely to differences in inflationary expectations.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
