         <fn id="d22e255a1310">
            <label>8</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d22e262" publication-type="other">
The PPP(PPI) figures in the chart are updated from OECD 1985 data using producer price indices
(PPIs), while the PPP(ULC) figures are updated with manufacturing unit labour costs. Full details of our
methodology are given in CSFB Economics (1989), and updated figures are published quarterly in
CSFB's 'Economic Prospects'.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
         <fn id="d22e278a1310">
            <label>9</label>
            <p>
               <mixed-citation id="d22e285" publication-type="other">
The forecast of a 3.15 PPP rate for the second quarter of 1991 assumes a 3 per cent per annum
differential between UK and German producer price inflation, approximately the figure prevailing over
the last three months.</mixed-citation>
            </p>
         </fn>
